  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting Children with Disabilities in Pakistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">MAITS&apos; award-winning Community Healthworker training teaches life-saving techniques that improve disabled children&apos;s health &amp; well-being, through expert volunteer trainers in Pakistan. We will equip local community workers with the skills to support families in their own homes. Piloted in Jamaica we taught simple techniques to carers of disabled children. Before our training, there were serious case reviews with children dying or very ill. After, there was not one serious case review or death.</narrative>
  </description>
